      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PEGRUM CITY (1) broke through for his maiden success two back but could manage only midfield last time when finished fourth and beaten 9 lengths at this track over 520m (30.89). Back to track where he won his maiden. Can turn form around here. WEST ON PASH (8) is progressing well with another good run last time, placing (30.58) last time out at this track. Has never missed the frame here at the trip from three starts. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Can feature again. RED HOT BONNIE (2) collided in the run but raced on speed and boxed on well, finishing a 2 length second (30.39) in a Novice race at this track. Harder here but expected to measure up. PLEASE ME (3) was well fancied in betting last start but could only manage 0.8 lengths away in second (30.24). Yet to win out of this box but has been in the placings three times from three starts. Well placed and gets her chance.",
